definition: to consider oneself unexcelled in the world/to be insufferably arrogant
can/may/able to/to approve/to permit/to suit/(particle used for emphasis) certainly/very
one/1/single/a (article)/as soon as/entire/whole/all/throughout/"one" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 1)/also pr. [yao1] for greater clarity when spelling out numbers digit by digit

sentences.english: We were on the side of the angels, and we triumphed against overwhelming odds.
sentences.chinese: 我們和天使是一夥兒的，戰勝了不可一世的魑魅魍魎。

sentences.english: A：Winning the spelling bee has really gone to Brian’s head.
sentences.chinese: 布萊恩在拼字比賽中拿了冠軍，讓他自覺不可一世。
曾經的我，總是不可一世。

sentences.english: That's how the family that haughtily enjoyed utmost privilege in Romania saw its demise.
sentences.chinese: 原本在羅國不可一世享盡特權的家族，竟是如此下場。

sentences.english: How insufferably arrogant for the love affair , like poison.
sentences.chinese: 這般如此不可一世的愛戀，就如同毒藥醉人。

sentences.english: Self-expansion, show its teeth, insufferably arrogant.
sentences.chinese: 自我膨脹，齜牙咧嘴，不可一世。

sentences.english: You are still paranoid that the juvenile. Insufferably arrogant.
sentences.chinese: 你始終還是那個偏執的少年，不可一世。

sentences.english: We got two very good results against two of the best teams in Europe.
sentences.chinese: 我們接連擊敗了兩支曾不可一世的歐洲豪門。

definition: the eye can see nothing worthwhile all around (idiom); arrogant/condescending/supercilious
bossy and domineering/throwing one's weight about
to show off one's military strength (idiom); to strut around/to bluff/to bluster
to look disdainfully out of the corner of one's eye
